OL,6,FAll of the women at Willowdene are
OL,7,Fcalled students. They work on the
OL,8,Ffarm, weighing sheep, milking cows,
OL,9,Fbetween twice weekly therapy sessions,
OL,10,Fand education classes. There are still
OL,11,Frules ` women can't leave the site or
OL,12,Fuse their mobile phones, but it is a
OL,13,Ffar stretch from the punitive rigidity
OL,14,Fof prison.
OL,16,FAs we walked around the fields, their
OL,17,FCEO Matt Home told us that for lots of
OL,18,Fwomen coming to Willowdene was harder
OL,19,Fthan prison.
